	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Famiclone with only black and white color [Solved]</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />It started just a few weeks ago<br />I was testing one of my homemade multicartridge which suddenly the color of the game turned into black and white!<br />I thought bad circuit of multicartridge caused the issue<br />I just admit it that I messed up with GPU which is inside of the CPU!<br />After fixing the Multicartridge it ran just fine but with no color<br />I noticed that it freezes randomly!<br />Then I thought it is again because of a bad cartridge and I tried adding some caps to it without no luck!<br />Yesterday I wanted to play a little with my Famiclone and I found out that it freezes very often with any cartridge!<br />I start searching for any unusual thing on the board <br />I found out that all the problem was because of the crystal loose pins which was caused by pressing eject button :<br /><br /><a href="http://8pic.ir/viewer.php?file=62809580040314434196.jpg" class="postlink"><img src="http://8pic.ir/images/62809580040314434196_thumb.jpg" alt="Image" /></a><br /><br /><a href="http://8pic.ir/viewer.php?file=31262798351200116467.jpg" class="postlink"><img src="http://8pic.ir/images/31262798351200116467_thumb.jpg" alt="Image" /></a><br /><br />So as a result a loose pin of the crystal can cause black and white color with random freeze!

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


